Ispa’al: The _ispa’al_ (אִתְפַּעַל) is one of the [[Aramaic binyanim]]. ([[{{Binyan}} is a special concept in Hebrew and Aramaic grammar]].)
- Verbs in the _ispa’al_ can be [[reflexive]], or [[passive]] and [[intensive]].
- The _ispa’al_ can correspond to either the [[pu’al]] and to the [[_hispa’el_]] in Hebrew.

- Ispe’el: The _ispe’el_ (אִתְפְּעֵל) is one of the [[Aramaic binyanim]]. ([[{{Binyan}} is a special concept in Hebrew and Aramaic grammar]].)
- Verbs in the _ispe’el_ have the properties of being [[active]] and [[causative]].
- The _ispe’el_ corresponds to the [[_hispa’el_]] in Hebrew, and specifically is the [[reflexive]] version of a [[_pa’el_]] verb.
